    "Verbal conversations with various stakeholders, such as clients, contractors, and community representatives, allow designers to understand their needs (Lawson and Loke, 1997; Dubberly and Pangaro, 2019) and constraints better and negotiate project requirements (McDonnell, 2009).",
    "Similarly, conversations among designers facilitate knowledge sharing and negotiation of new ideas, allowing design teams to transcend the individual abilities of a single designer (Arias et al., 2000)."
